{
  "texts": [
    "Over the last decades, many methods, with AI and machine learning (ML) being at the forefront, have been developed and successfully implemented at several stages of drug design, starting from disease identification to clinical trials.",
    "This extensive focus on AI research is exponentially growing, as evident from the number of scholarly outputs published over the years (Fig. 1).",
    "With the rapid advances in computer-based technology, computational methods have quickly become indispensable for medical research.",
    "For instance, in the past decades, many efforts have been put into developing computational chemistry tools that can predict drug properties and their interactions in silico.",
    "Such tools have helped reduce the heavy dependence on wet-lab measurements, which tend to be expensive and time-consuming."
  ]
}